--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
README : MetaQuant
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MetaQuant is a metagenomic abundance profiling tool. It uses an online variational
Bayes algorithm to estimate relative genome abundances of microbial species in a
complex microbial community sample.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I.   Authors:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The abundance estimation algorithm was developed by Kevin McLoughlin at
Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory. Some of the source code in MetaQuant is
adapted from the "eXpress" RNA-seq quantification tool, which was developed by 
Adam Roberts and Lior Pachter at UC Berkeley. Adam Roberts designed and wrote 
eXpress. 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
II.  Requirements:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MetaQuant is a standalone tool that requires gcc 4.0 or greater, and runs on Linux 
and Macintosh OS X.

It depends on Boost (http://www.boost.org), 
BamTools (https://github.com/pezmaster31/bamtools),
and ZLIB (http://zlib.net/).


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
III. Learn More (Installation, Manual, etc.):
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Installation steps, tutorial, manual, documentation, etc. are all available 
from the MetaQuant github repository.

